  "id": "phekb-sleep-apnea-comprehensive",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "sleep-apnea",
  "name": "Sleep Apnea - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Procedures)",
  "description": "Simulates a sleep specialist identifying their complete sleep apnea patient population. Combines: sleep apnea diagnosis codes (multiple subtypes) and polysomnography procedures. Tests Condition + Procedure resource union.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete sleep apnea patient population for a quality improvement initiative on CPAP adherence. From clinical experience, sleep apnea patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal sleep apnea diagnosis (obstructive, central, or mixed sleep apnea, across all severity levels), and most have undergone polysomnography for diagnosis.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any sleep apnea diagnosis (sleep apnea NOS, OSA syndrome, central sleep apnea, OSA of adult, mixed sleep apnea)\n2. Patients who have undergone polysomnography\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found.",
